  "texts": [
    "Deep Learning for Medical Image Analysis and CADCNN's beginnings may be traced back to the nonrecognition idea put out by [114] in the beginning 1980 s. In early 1990, [115] training a CNN using backpropagation to categories sequences of character recognition.",
    "In the initial nineties, CNN was employed in several domains including image identification, character segmentation and facial detection.",
    "In 1993, [116] trained a CNN to recognize pulmonary nodules in chest radiographs, which was the first time CNN had been used to analyze healthcare images [117].",
    "Chan et al. [118][119][120][121] used CNN for lung nodules and microcalcification recognition [122,123] on radiography within the identical year.",
    "In 1994, [124] used a comparable shift-invariant neural network to find regions of microcalcifications."
  ],
